CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1783711191
OL,3,CBayeux Tapestry arrives in England
OL,4,Cafter secret overnight journey from
OL,5,CFrance
OL,7,FStitched in wool thread on linen
OL,8,Ffabric, the artwork depicts the events
OL,9,Fleading up to the Battle of Hastings
OL,10,Fin October 1066, when William, Duke of
OL,11,FNormandy, defeated King Harald's Anglo-
OL,12,FSaxon army. The invasion ended Saxon
OL,13,Frule and made William the Conqueror
OL,14,Fthe first Norman king of England.
OL,16,FHistorians believe the tapestry was
OL,17,Fcommissioned by Bishop Odo of Bayeux,
OL,18,FWilliam's half-brother, and was
OL,19,Fprobably sewn by women in England `
OL,20,Fpossibly nuns ` before being taken
OL,21,Facross the Channel.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1783711191
OL,3,CBayeux Tapestry arrives in England
OL,4,Cafter secret overnight journey from
OL,5,CFrance
OL,7,FIt has spent most of the last
OL,8,Fmillennium in the town of Bayeux in
OL,9,Fnorthwest France, apart from two short
OL,10,Fperiods at the Louvre in Paris.
OL,12,FThe loan was secured during a state
OL,13,Fvisit to the UK by French President
OL,14,FEmmanuel Macron in July and coincides
OL,15,Fwith a renovation of the museum where
OL,16,Fit normally resides in Bayeux.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
